The storage and thermal stabilities of RIMRs are very important to practical applications. Regarding the storage stability (see Fig. 3a), the half-life (the storage time that 50% of the initial activity can be retained after the incubation in reaction buffer at 4 °C) is about 2.6 days for the free RuBisCO, and it is enhanced to be three times (8 days) after the immobilization. In addition, the storage stability of the immobilized RuBisCO is enhanced by 7.2 times compared with the free one (43% vs. 6% of the initial activity retention) after the incubation for 15 days. More characterizations of free RuBisCO under different incubation time including sodium dodecyl sulfate–polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis (SDS–PAGE) are provided in Supplementary Fig. 11.Fig. 3
