The protein-loading capacity of the PDA-modified microfluidic reactors was investigated to select an optimal RuBisCO concentration for the RIMRs fabrication in the following research. Increased concentrations of RuBisCO solutions (1.5625–25 μg μL−1) were injected into the PDA-modified microfluidic reactors. Then, the rinsed-out RuBisCO solutions were carefully collected to determine the protein concentration difference between the initially injected and the rinsed-out RuBisCO solutions. The protein concentration was qualified by the Bradford method68 using the Quick Start Bradford Protein Assay kit (Bio-Rad Pacific Limited.), which were determined by measuring the absorbance at the wavelength of 595 nm using a UV–visible spectrometer (UV-2450, Shimadzu). BSA solutions (0.125–1 mg mL−1) were selected as standards to plot the calibration curve (see Supplementary Fig. 7). The protein-loading amount of the reactor was calculated by1protein-loadingamountμg⋅cm-2=(C0Vi-C1Vw)∕Ar\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
